<2ND_LINE>AM-Jobless-Entrepreneurs, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0403,120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three States to Try Turning Jobless Into Entrepreneurs</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS lede to delete extraneous words</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three states _ Oregon, Massachusetts and
Minnesota _ will test giving some laid off workers their
unemployment compensation benefits in lump sums for use in starting
their own businesses.
   The Labor Department said the demonstration project authorized
by Congress last year will divert about $8 million in the
unemployment insurance fund to helping between 1,000 2,000
beneficiaries ``become successful entrepreneurs.''
   The program would provide cash allowances equal to the amount
laid off workers would normally receive in weekly unemployment
insurance benefits, the department said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
