<2ND_LINE>PM-Box Office,0336</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>`Alien Nation' Leads Box Office Sweepstakes</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JEFF WILSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Alien Nation,'' starring James Caan as a
seasoned veteran cop paired with a crime-fighting humanoid from
another planet, earned $8.4 million to become the box office leader
in its first week of release.
   ``Punchline'' finished second with $5.2 million while ``Gorillas
in the Mist'' was third with $4 million.
   Amy Irving's ``Crossing Delancey'' was fourth and the dark
comedy ``A Fish Called Wanda,'' in its 13th week, was fifth.
   The Bruce Willis action adventure ``Die Hard'' took sixth, the
John Lennon documentary ``Imagine'' was seventh, followed by ``Who
Framed Roger Rabbit.''
   The father-son conflict comedy ``Memories of Me'' was ninth and
Tom Cruise's ``Cocktail'' was 10th.
   Here are the top movies for the weekend as tallied by Exhibitor
Relations Inc., with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater
screens, average per screen, total gross and number of weeks in
release.
   1. ``Alien Nation,'' 20th Century Fox, $8.42 million, 1,430
screens, $5,889 per screen, $8.42 million, one week.
   2. ``Punchline,'' Columbia, $5.21 million, 753 screens, $6,914
per screen, $5.47 million, two weeks.
   3. ``Gorillas in the Mist,'' Universal, $4.04 million, 1,081
screens, $3,740 per screen, $9.2 million, three weeks.
   4. ``Crossing Delancey,'' Warner Bros., $1.66 million, 290
screens, $5,733 per screen, $7.35 million, six weeks.
   5. ``A Fish Called Wanda,'' MGM@UA, $1.63 million, 959 screens,
$1,706 per screen, $53.32 million, 13 weeks.
   6. ``Die Hard,'' 20th Century Fox, $1.51 million, 1,050 screens,
$1,441 per screen, $72.77 million, 13 weeks.
   7. ``Imagine: John Lennon,'' Warner Bros., $1.41 million, 561
screens, $2,517 per screen, $1.41 million, one week.
   8. ``Who Framed Roger Rabbit,'' Disney, $1.4 million, 1,147
screens, $1,224 per screen, $141.98 million, 16 weeks.
   9. ``Memories of Me,'' MGM@UA, $1.39 million, 723 screens,
$1,919 per screen, $1.49 million, two weeks.
   10. ``Cocktail,'' Disney, $1.28 million, 1,042 screens, $1,227
per screen, $69.22 million, 11 weeks.
