   Arthur Ashe, the former Wimbledon and U.S.
Open champion, is here looking to develop an untapped pool of
tennis talent in America's inner cities.
   ``With the proper training and supervision, their skills can be
honed to compete with the greats,'' Ashe said of the 500 Newark
youngsters learning about tennis at his free clinic.
   Ashe and Nick Bollettieri, who operates some of the nation's
finest tennis clinics, are teaching the game this week at three
city parks as part of a $83,000 program paid for by the city, Essex
County, the Newark Board of Education and the city's Boys and Girls
clubs.
