<HEAD>Officer Shoots Self in Foot A Second Time</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAS CRUCES, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   For the second time in two weeks, a Las
Cruces policeman has shot himself accidentally in the right foot.
   Officer Bill Schatzman, 23, was off duty when he entered his
home Sunday evening and dropped his .45-caliber pistol, which
fired, said Police Chief Ron J. Axtell.
   On Sept. 28, Schatzman was off duty when he was removing an
automatic from his holster and the gun accidentally discharged,
also wounding him in the right foot, police said.
   The department requires that police weapons be secure, but
Axtell said he was not sure those rules could be enforced if an
officer carries his weapon while he is off duty.
   ``I'm not saying he did anything wrong,'' Axtell said. ``It's
something we'll have to look into.''
   Schatzman was listed in good condition Tuesday at Memorial
General Hospital in Las Cruces, said hospital spokeswoman Lori
Allen.
