<2ND_LINE>AM-Barricade-Slayings,0203</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gunman Kills Two, Surrenders After Standoff</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman shot and killed two people, then hid
in an apartment building for nearly four hours before surrendering
to police Tuesday, authorities said.
   The gunman, whose identity was not immediately known,
surrendered about 9:20 p.m., said Cmdr. William Booth, a police
spokesman.
   ``There was no gunfire exchanged,'' Booth said. ``SWAT officers
gave him the option of coming out and surrendering and he did.''
   The woman was shot about 5:30 p.m. at the apartment complex on
the west side of the city, said Sgt. John Gambill.
   ``The suspect fled to the rear after the female was shot and
killed at the scene,'' he said. ``After that, he ran into another
man and for an unknown reason that man was shot.''
   The second victim died later at the University of California at
Los Angeles Medical Center.
   Later, the gunman barricaded himself into an apartment, Gambill
said. A SWAT team went to the apartment complex and surrounded the
area after the gunman ran inside.
   Investigators could not immediately determine a motive for the
slayings. The identities of the victims were not immediately known.
