<HEAD>Fire Hits L.A. Library For Third Time In Three Years</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN ANTCZAK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Arson investigators probed the third fire in
less than three years at the downtown Central Library, where
hundreds of thousands of books were destroyed in two 1986 arson
blazes.
   Because the building is undergoing extensive renovation, no
books were in the library when the fire broke out Tuesday. However,
authorities feared that smoke from the basement blaze may have
again damaged the structure's huge murals.
