Wyman Jones, surveying the scene after being summoned by Fire Chief
Donald Manning.
   A passer-by reported the fire at 5:17 p.m. and it was declared
extinguished a half-hour later, said Assistant Fire Chief Gerald
Johnson. The blaze was confined to paper and wood construction
material in an 8-by-25-foot basement room.
   The work being done in that room involved removal of ceiling
tiles containing asbestos. The presence of the hazardous material
worried firefighters and prevented library officials from
immediately entering afterward to assess the damage.
