<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Border Guard,0119</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Uniformed Czechoslovak Border Guard Flees to Austria</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A uniformed Czechoslovak border guard
crossed the border into Austria early Wednesday and applied for
political asylum at a police station, a police spokesman said.
   The 20-year-old Czechoslovak, identified only as Karel K., fled
over the border at Gmuend, 70 miles northwest of Vienna, at 6 a.m.,
said the spokesman from the police station.
   The guard fired shots into the air while still on Czechoslovak
territory, but did not injure anyone, the spokesman said.
   He said the guard crossed into Austria with the intention of
seeking asylum in the West. He was brought to the main refugee camp
of Traiskirchen outside Vienna.
</TEXT>
