<TEXT>
   The outlawed Irish Republican
Army claimed responsbility Wednesday for a shooting in a Belfast
ice cream parlor in which an off-duty policeman was killed and two
customers were injured.
   The IRA, which is fighting to end British rule in Northern
Ireland, made the claim in a statement to Belfast news media.
