<HEAD>31 Children Taken To Hospital After Bus Accident</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with eight children hospitalized with
minor injuries, children's ages, driver's son on bus hospitalized.
CORRECTS number of students to 31 sted 30</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NORTH LOGAN, Utah (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A school bus ran off a road, jumped
into a ditch and landed in a field Wednesday, sending 31 children
to a hospital, authorities said.
   No serious injuries were reported, but Cache County School
District spokesman Keith Hansen said eight children remained
hospitalized late Wednesday with injuries ranging from a fractured
leg to minor head and abdominal injuries.
   All the children were from the Newton area, authorities said,
and ranged in age from 5 to 10.
   The bus was carrying 64 children between Newton and Trenton and
was en route to the Lewiston Elementary School when the driver was
distracted by a child asking a question, Hansen said.
   ``The bus went off the shoulder of the road and in order to keep
it from rolling over, the driver jumped a canal and the bus landed
in a field,'' Hansen said.
   He said the driver, Ned Phelps, has driven school buses for many
years.
   Hansen said Phelps was ``extremely shaken'' and was kept at the
hospital for observation.
   Phelps' son, Sam Phelps, 8, was one of the children hospitalized.
</TEXT>
