<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A senior federal judge has accused defense
lawyers of ethical misconduct in the Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc.
securities-fraud case, escalating what has become a hot-tempered
courtroom battle pitting the octogenarian jurist against some of
the nation's best-paid legal talent.
   Judge Milton Pollack made the accusations Tuesday in response to
defense efforts to have him disqualified on grounds his wife,
Moselle, stands to gain about $30 million from the sale of her
stock in Palais Royal, a Houston company going private in a deal
